			    STPJS 217</div>
  <div class="topic">Men are Saved Through Obedience to Knowledge</div>
  <p class="std">We have thieves among us, adulterers,<span class="footRef">1</span> liars, hypocrites.<span class="footRef">2</span> If God should speak from heaven,<span class="footRef">3</span>
  he would command you not to steal, not to commit adultery, not to covet, nor deceive,<span class="footRef">4</span> but be
  faithful over a few things.<span class="footRef">5</span> As far as we degenerate from God, we descend to the devil and lose
  knowledge,<span class="footRef">6</span> and without knowledge we cannot be saved,<span class="footRef">7</span> and while our hearts are filled with evil,<span class="footRef">8</span>
  and we are studying evil,<span class="footRef">9</span> there is no room in our hearts for good,<span class="footRef">10</span> or studying good. Is not God
  good?<span class="footRef">11</span> Then you be good;<span class="footRef">12</span> if He is faithful,<span class="footRef">13</span> then you be faithful.<span class="footRef">14</span> Add to your faith virtue, to
  virtue knowledge,<span class="footRef">15</span> and seek for every good thing.<span class="footRef">16</span></p>
  <p class="std">The Church must be cleansed,<span class="footRef">17</span> and I proclaim against all iniquity. A man is saved no faster
  than he gets knowledge,<span class="footRef">18</span> for if he does not get knowledge, he will be brought into captivity by some
  evil power<span class="footRef">19</span> in the other world, as evil spirits will have more knowledge, and consequently more
  power<span class="footRef">20</span> than many men who are on the earth. Hence it needs revelation to assist us, and give us
  knowledge of the things of God.<span class="footRef">21</span></p>
  <p class="std">What is the reason that the Priests of the day do not get revelation? They ask only to consume
  it upon their lusts.<span class="footRef">22</span> Their hearts are corrupt,<span class="footRef">23</span> and they cloak their iniquity by saying there are no
  more revelations.<span class="footRef">24</span> But if any revelations are given of God, they are universally opposed by the
  priests and Christendom at large; for they reveal their wickedness and abominations.<span class="footRef">25</span> (April 10,
  1842.) DHC 4:588.</p>
  <div class="topic">Baptism for the Dead</div>
  <p class="std">The great designs of God<span class="footRef">26</span> in relation to the salvation of the human family, are very little
  understood by the professedly wise and intelligent generation in which we live. Various and
  conflicting are the opinions of men concerning the plan of salvation, the requisitions of the
  Almighty, the necessary preparations for heaven, the state and condition of departed spirits,<span class="footRef">27</span> and
  the happiness or misery that is consequent upon the practice of righteousness and iniquity according
  to their several notions of virtue and vice.</p>
  <p class="std">The Mussulman condemns the heathen, the Jew, and the Christian, and the whole world of
  mankind that reject his Koran, as infidels,<span class="footRef">28</span> and consigns the whole of them to perdition.<span class="footRef">29</span></p>
